This article discusses President Obama's plan to make America a magnet for jobs by investing in manufacturing. The plan includes several key initiatives such as partnering with businesses and communities to invest in American-made technologies and workers, ending tax breaks for companies that ship jobs overseas, bringing jobs back to hard-hit manufacturing towns, and opening new markets for American-made products. The President also proposes investing in manufacturing innovation institutes, launching a Community College to Career Fund, reforming the tax code to make the U.S. more competitive, and strengthening manufacturing supply chains. Additionally, the article highlights efforts to attract investment to the U.S., support American exports, enforce trade laws, promote clean energy and advanced vehicle manufacturing, and increase federal research and development in advanced manufacturing technologies.